INTRALAB_AYUDA_INFORMES_INDIV:
Surname: Use this option if you know the surname of the patient you want to look foR. Type in the full surname or just a prefix. I.e: SURNAME. If any patient match the search condition the system will show a list (sorted by date and starting byt the newest) allowing the user to choose the desired patient he wants to select. If a number of patients bigger that the number the system is able to visualize matches the search, a message will be shown and the maximum number of patients will be shown. If the list does not contain the desired patient narrow the search condition so that all the matching patients will show on screen.

ID Card: Patients can also be queried by Identity Card number or passport. Use this option if this number is available as the search will be narrower than searching by surname.

Social Security Number (aka SSN): Use this option when querying by Social Security Number.

National Health Service Number (aka NHS): Use this option when querying by Sanitary Card Number.

History: Set the clinical history number of the patient you want to review. Searching by clinical history (or any code) will always be more accurate than by surnames.

Wildcards can be used to search for patients and orders.

An underscore (_) can be used when a character in a specific location is not known.

A percent sign (%) can be used when a string of characters is not known.

Examples:

- Searching 'ma%' returns results as Martin, Matthew, Macgowan.

- Searching '%son' returns results as Jason, Jefferson, Watson.

- Searching '%wa%' returns results as Macgowan, Watson, Sawana.

- Searching 'gonz_le%' returns results as González, Gonzalez, Gonzales.

- Searching '%m%t%' returns results as Smith, Ameeta, Remington.

- Searching '%16' returns results as 00000016, 00000216, 00005216.

- Searching '%1%6%' returns results as 12345678, 00010060.
